title: Bobbysocks (1st album - 1985)
description:
This is their debut album. Originally released in 1984, it was latter re-launched in 1985, when Bobbysocks won the Eurovision Song Contest with "La det Swinge" (Let it Swing). For the 1985 edition, the original opening track "In The Mud" (Farewell Blues Ã¢â‚¬â€œ In The Mood) was removed and replaced by "Let it Swing".

This 2nd edition was the one released worldwide, gaining a lot of popularity, specially in the nordic countries. It topped the norwegian charts and reached the Gold status.

After that, Bobbysocks recorded two more albums: "Waiting for the Morning" in 1986 (which became an even bigger success with it's Platinum certification), and "Walkin' on Air" in 1987, which became Gold.

In 1988, after 4 successful years, the duo disbanded, resuming the girls their respective solo careers.
